description._content: Collection: NASA Great Images in Nasa Collection Title: Earth from Apollo 8 Full Description: This is how the Earth looked as photographed from a point near the Moon by the Apollo 8 astronauts. The Earth fills less than one percent of the frame exposed through 80mm lens. North is approximately vertical. Kinda lonely, isn't it? Date: 12/01/1968 NASA Center: Johnson Space Center Image #: AS8-16-2606 Original url: grin.hq.nasa.gov/ABSTRACTS/GPN-2000-001489.html UID: SPD-GRIN-GPN-2000-00 1489 Center: JSC Center Number: AS8-16-2606 GRIN DataBase Number: GPN-2000-001489 SOURCE: nasaimages.org/luna/servlet/detail/nasaNAS~5~5~21728~126475 Visit www.nasaimages.org for the most comprehensive compilation of NASA stills, film and video, created in partnership with Internet Archive.
